(486, '4', '2022-11-20 15:32:15', '<img src=\"http://www.automobilesreview.com/uploads/2009/11/chevrolet-cruze-thumb.jpg\" alt=\"Chevrolet Cruze at 2009 Los Angeles International Auto Show\" />Almost every single manufacturer is trying to reduce the fuel consumption and the CO2 emission of their cars and Chevrolet is not an exception. The all-new Cruze will make its U.S. premiere at the 2009 LA Auto Show. Besides Cruze, other vehicles, which will be on display are Volt, Camaro, Equinox and much more hot-selling [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.automobilesreview.com/auto-news/chevrolet-cruze-at-2009-los-angeles-international-auto-show/19843/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.automobilesreview.com</a><br>', 'Chevrolet Cruze at 2009 Los Angeles International Auto Show'),
(487, '4', '2022-11-20 16:29:40', '<img src=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/TrackPass_header-500x186.jpg\" alt=\"TrackPass_header\" />\nThe answers to our little NASCAR trivia test were a little tricky, yet we had a bunch of folks who got them all right. Just for the record, here are the questions and answers:\nWhere was NASCAR’s first road race held?\nSorry Mr Robertson, Riverside was a good guess but was incorrect. The original track on Daytona [...]...<br><a href=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/the-winner-and-a-chance-to-win-another-nascar-trackpass/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: thegarageblog.com</a><br>', 'The winner and a chance to win another NASCAR TrackPass'),
(490, '4', '2022-11-20 15:31:26', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/chrysler_jeep_dodge_dealership.jpg\" alt=\"Chrysler Jeep Dodge Dealership\" />\nBack in June when Chrysler emerged from a U.S. government funded bankruptcy it terminated nearly 800 dealerships in an effort to keep its network size in line with its U.S. market share. Chrysler came out of bankruptcy court with about 2,400 dealerships and had 2,366 at the end of October. The Auburn Hills automaker is [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/ACo1WK7hbIM/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Chrysler may close another 100 dealerships'),
