(495, '4', '2022-11-20 17:24:40', '<img src=\"http://www.automobilesreview.com/uploads/2009/11/vath-ml-63-amg-thumb.jpg\" alt=\"VÄTH Mercedes-Benz ML63 AMG\" />VÄTH Automobiltechnik created a monster on base of Mercedes-Benz ML63 AMG. The mighty SUV reaches 300km/h and its refined engine now develops 585 HP and really exciting 690Nm of torque. This is the most powerful non-turbocharged V8 in the world.\nThe engine tuning cost 17,850 Euro plus additional 1,785 Euro for the installation. It includes: enlarged [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.automobilesreview.com/auto-news/vath-mercedes-benz-ml63-amg/19849/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.automobilesreview.com</a><br>', 'VÄTH Mercedes-Benz ML63 AMG'),
(498, '4', '2022-11-20 17:01:59', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/BlogBanner.jpg\" alt=\"BlogBanner\" />\n+ Yesterday we served up our impressions of the 2010 BMW 535i GT, and today BMW announced pricing for the range-topping 550i GT. [Car and Driver]\n+ Aptera Motors announces a delay in the introduction of its three-wheeled electric vehicle, the 2e, along with news that it will be cutting down on staff.  [Car and Driver]\n+ [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:Daily Downshift: November 2, 2009Daily Downshift: November 12, 2009Daily Downshift: November 16, 2009...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/yAyk0yCbxWs/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Daily Downshift: November 19, 2009'),
(501, '5', '2022-11-20 17:47:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/www.autoblog.com/media/2009/09/prius_plug-in_frankfurt.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: EV/Plug-in, Hybrid, Toyota\n\n Toyota Prius Plug-in Hybrid Concept -- Click above for high-res image gallery\n\nToyota is getting ready to start deploying a fleet of 200 plug-in Prius hybrids in the coming months and the company needs to figure out what to do with them. The cars will all be leased for purposes of field testing. Toyota is now in discussions with federal and local governments and energy companies about who will get how many of the lithium ion battery Priuses. The company is looking for towns and cities that are, \"actively promoting environmentally considerate vehicles.\"...<br><a href=\"http://green.autoblog.com/2009/11/20/toyota-starts-discussions-on-who-will-get-phev-priuses/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: green.autoblog.com</a><br>', 'Toyota starts discussions on who will get PHEV Priuses'),
(502, '5', '2022-11-20 18:26:43', 'Exide Technologies has entered a new contract with Toyota Motor Corp. for the sale of 105,000 more batteries each year to the carmaker. The deal also boosts the battery company’s shares. In a statement by Exide, the lead-acid starting batteries will go into the Highlander, a mid-size crossover SUV, built at Toyota’s plant in Princeton, [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/toyota-planning-to-use-exide-batteries-for-its-highlander-suvs/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Toyota planning to use Exide batteries for its Highlander SUVs'),
(503, '5', '2022-11-20 18:04:10', 'Don’t get too excited now but it could well be possible that Rolls-Royce will have an electric Phantom on the road within a year and just in time for the car to be one of the centerpieces of BMW’s sponsorship of the 2012 London Olympics. It’s well-known that company boss Tom Purvis wants to produce [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/rumor-electric-rolls-royce-phantom-coming-within-the-next-12-months/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Rumor: Electric Rolls-Royce Phantom coming within the next 12 months'),
(506, '5', '2022-11-20 17:37:33', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/2009_ford_focus_rs_wide_main_a.jpg\" alt=\"2009 Ford Focus RS\" />\nWhen Ford first introduced the new Focus RS to the European market, it had planned to produce only 1,200 units. However, due to high-demand, Ford of Europe has decided to build an additional 400 units of the 305-hp Ford hatchback – exclusively for sale in German.\nFord said that this is the final decision and that [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/Db5mV6EaeCs/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'This is it: Ford to produce another 400 units of the 2009 Focus RS'),
(511, '5', '2022-11-20 17:35:26', 'The green category seemed a little subdued this year, and there were a lot of cars we’d already seen during previous visits to SEMA. Still, that didn’t stop us from finding some real standouts in the zero-emissions, electric, hybrid, and alt-fuel divisions–showing that green performance is still alive and well. For one thing, there was [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/cardomain/~3/PxYDeyENHss/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Best of SEMA: Green Cars'),
(514, '5', '2022-11-20 19:15:27', 'General Motors Co. is predicting an increase in its US market share and annual sales rate for the month of November. Mike DiGiovanni, executive director of global market and industry analysis, said that they expect GM’s market share in the US to rise for the fourth consecutive month in November. He also forecasts that the [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/gms-us-market-share-may-rise-for-the-fourth-straight-month-in-november/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'GM’s U.S. market share may rise for the fourth straight month in November'),
(516, '5', '2022-11-20 18:42:44', 'A Russian bidder has reportedly offered to buy 40% of Renault’s Formula One team, according to Finland’s Turun Sanomat. The deal could potentially result in the Russian Vitaly Petrov’s signing to be Robert Kubica’s team-mate. This could explain Timo Glock’s move to Manor Grand Prix, despite his earlier strong links to the French squad.\nAdrian Newey [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/rumor-renault-to-sell-40-percent-of-its-f1-team/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Rumor: Renault to sell 40 percent of its F1 team'),
(518, '5', '2022-11-20 18:55:49', 'This week’s ebay Motors Showdown really hit a chord with people. Even with our ongoing commenting issues (now even I can’t comment, and yes, we are working on it) we got a HUGE response on this one. At first it looked like the IROC was gonna walk away with it, but then the Fox body rallied, and in the end [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/cardomain/~3/n6bGUNKqYxQ/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'IROC vs. 5.0: Too Close to Call!'),
(524, '5', '2022-11-20 20:06:37', '<img src=\"http://www.carzi.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/kimi-raikkonen.jpg\" alt=\"kimi raikkonen\" />\n\n\n\n\nJust before the inaugural Abu Dhabi Grand Prix, Arabian Business magazine published the salaries of several current drivers. MSN has an article listing the salaries, along with an interesting Points Per Million Dollars Spent Ratio. So which team got the best bang for their buck in terms of dollars spent on driver versus points earned [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Carzi/~3/CN7g2SmXgSc/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Formula 1 Driver Salaries'),
(530, '5', '2022-11-20 20:33:30', '<img src=\"http://www.wired.com/images_blogs/autopia/2009/11/vw_touareg_dakar_01.jpg\" alt=\"vw_touareg_dakar_01\" />\nThe Paris-Dakar Rally is a race so crazy competitors have been taken out by land mines. To say it’s grueling is like saying Carrie Prejean likes shooting video. Just what sort of vehicle is required to take on a race where normal conditions include searing heat, towering dunes, ginormous rocks and weather conditions that would [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.wired.com/~r/wiredautopia/~3/hi9tDO3hjFM/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.wired.com</a><br>', 'VW Builds the World’s Coolest SUV'),
(532, '5', '2022-11-20 19:44:37', '<img src=\"http://www.wired.com/images_blogs/autopia/2009/11/chevrolet_volt_plug.jpg\" alt=\"chevrolet_volt_plug\" />\nCalifornia is the birthplace of the coming EV invasion, but a tiny town in Iowa wants to be the birthplace of a “Pony Express” of charging stations that will keep those cars going.\nBusinessman Mike Howard has erected four charging stations in Elk Horn, a town of 650 people about an hour east of Omaha. He [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.wired.com/~r/wiredautopia/~3/sB4n31NgVGc/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.wired.com</a><br>', 'Welcome to Iowa. Please Plug In Your Car.'),
(533, '5', '2022-11-20 01:06:57', '<img src=\"http://www.wired.com/images_blogs/autopia/2009/11/john_surtees_ev_hunnel.jpg\" alt=\"john_surtees_ev_hunnel\" />\nHow cool is John Surtees? At 75 years old, the racing legend isn’t slowing down. The motorcycle and F1 champ decided it would be fun to drive a Ginetta electric vehicle through the English Channel Tunnel, or the Chunnel, as they so cleverly call it.\nWhy? To mark the 15th anniversary of the Tunnel’s opening, of [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.wired.com/~r/wiredautopia/~3/e8-mvdiDPIc/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.wired.com</a><br>', 'John Surtees Drives an EV Across the Channel'),
(534, '5', '2022-11-19 23:50:25', '<img src=\"http://www.wired.com/images_blogs/autopia/2009/11/rolls_royce_phantom.jpg\" alt=\"rolls_royce_phantom\" />\nRumors of an electric Rolls-Royce Phantom are back, with the word being the super-luxe automaker could have one on the road within 12 months.\nWe’ve been hearing mumbling about this car for more than a year. It started when CEO Tom Purves said an e-Rolls would be perfect for well-heeled city dwellers. The car, he said, [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.wired.com/~r/wiredautopia/~3/gzBlMFFGaRo/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.wired.com</a><br>', 'Electric Rolls-Royce, In Time For Christmas 2010'),
