(832, '0', '2022-11-24 03:14:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/uk.autoblog.com/media/2009/11/000_daciaduster.png\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Dacia , News \nDacia are transforming themselves from a budget manufacturer into a lifestyle retailer. Exciting designs such as the Duster, already in the pipeline and now being prepared for launch in 2010, and the bang-up-to-date Sandero Stepway are grabbing attention. The Stepway has already successfully debuted in South America, where it is marketed as a Renault and should appeal to image-conscious customers on a tight budget here in Europe. Boasting Renault engineering, offering a long guarantee and representing excellent value for money, the Stepway is sure to make new friends...<br><a href=\"http://uk.autoblog.com/2009/11/24/outsider-view-on-the-way-up/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: uk.autoblog.com</a><br>', 'Outsider view: On the way up'),
