(912, '0', '2022-11-24 19:33:07', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/cadillac_escalade_platinum_wide_main_a.jpg\" alt=\"Cadillac Escalade Platinum\" />\nIt was rumored last year that GM’s full-size SUVs and pickups will move from a body-on-frame to a unibody construction. Well, seems like that rumor can now be laid to rest. Cosma International, a division of Magna International, announced today that it will supply the Detroit automaker with frame assembly for its next-generation full-size light [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/2LCGzr0KaB0/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'GM’s full-size pickups and SUVs to remain on body-on-frame construction'),
