(964, '0', '2022-11-25 00:13:03', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/2010_dodge_viper_acr_laguna_images_main.jpg\" alt=\"Dodge Viper SRT-10 ACR at Laguna SCEA\" />\nThe 2010 Viper SRT10 ACR has been hanging out at Laguna SECA all day with Dodge president and CEO Ralph Gilles and driver Chris Winkler. The group has just wrapped up the exciting day by breaking the Laguna Seca track production car lap record with a new time of 1:33.944. But before we get into all that [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/i4iHvCeq46Y/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'BREAKING: 2010 Dodge Viper ACR breaks Laguna SECA record, will debut at 2009 LA Auto Show'),
(965, '0', '2022-11-25 00:05:15', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/2010_honda_insight_hybrid_red_a.jpg\" alt=\"2010 Honda Insight Hybrid\" />\nPreliminary figures released by the EPA on Friday indicate that Honda Motor Co. has the most fuel efficient line of cars in the United States, reports Detroit News.  Hyundai Motor Co. came in a close second.\nAll vehicles sold in the 2009 model year are expected to average 21.1 miles per gallon in “real world” [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/vQPoC3ID9XU/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Honda’s vehicle lineup leads in fuel-efficiney in 2009 so far'),
(966, '0', '2022-11-24 23:59:17', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/2010_ford_fusion_hybrid_main_a.jpg\" alt=\"2010 Ford Fusion Hybrid\" />\nAmericans are slowly but surely warming up to fuel-efficient vehicles.  According to the EPA, new U.S. vehicles sold in 2008 averaged 21 mpg, up from 20.6 mpg in 2007, and they estimate that 2009 should average 21.1 mpg.\n“Gas prices have risen each year from 2002 to 2008; industry has failed to keep pace by [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/100PllAfH7s/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'EPA: Sales of fuel-efficient vehicles increasing slowly'),
(967, '0', '2022-11-25 00:29:34', '<img src=\"http://www.carzi.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/ferrari-club-victoria-show-500x251.jpg\" alt=\"ferrari club victoria show\" />\n\n\n\n\nOn November 15, 2009, the Ferrari Club Victoria Australia held a fundraiser show to raise support for one of the communities affected by bush fires earlier in the year.  It was a great turn out considering it’s 100km from Melbourne. Check out all the pictures of the FCV Show HERE.  Ferrari Club Victoria [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Carzi/~3/ydAAJWJgpII/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Ferrari Club of Victoria Australia Show Pictures'),
(968, '0', '2022-11-24 23:57:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/www.autoblog.com/media/2009/04/nyas-imiev-11_opt.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Hatchback, Mitsubishi, Electric\r\nMitsubishi i MiEV - Click above for high-res image gallery\r\n\r\nMitsubishi already plans on selling its little MiEV electric car in the U.S. within the next 18 months, and it appears that we may get a gasoline powered version of the roomy micro car as well. Automotive News is reporting that Mitsubishi is mulling the idea of putting petrol power in charge of propulsion of some i models, giving dealers a higher volume line that can compete with the Smart Fortwo. The automaker already sells a gasoline powered i in Europe, but Mitsubishi Motors North Ame...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogsinc/autoblog/~3/dxE-suo-kT0/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'REPORT: Mitsubishi considering gasoline-engine MiEV'),
