(973, '0', '2022-11-25 01:26:39', 'Aside from importing the i-MiEV electric minicar, Mitsubishi may also be giving U.S. dealers a gasoline version of the little four-passenger car. The i-MiEV would be competing against the Smart minicar. The Smart is imported from Europe, where Daimler AG builds it using a Mitsubishi engine. The gasoline-powered i-MiEV is actually already being sold in [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/mitsubishi-planning-to-introduce-gasoline-powered-i-miev-in-the-us/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Mitsubishi planning to introduce gasoline-powered i-MiEV in the U.S.'),
