(1038, '2', '2022-11-25 16:07:17', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/chevrolet_volt_blind_test.jpg\" alt=\"Chevrolet Volt Blind Pedestrian Test\" />\nGeneral Motors and the National Federation of the Blind are cooperating are teaming up to identify a safe level of sound to alert pedestrians without sight that a silent-running electric or hybrid vehicle is present.\n“We are confident electric vehicles can produce a safe and acceptable level of sound to alert blind pedestrians to their presence,” [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/uf1q0hL_mDw/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Video: Chevrolet Volt will make ‘chirping’ sound to alert blind pedestrians'),
(1039, '2', '2022-11-25 15:55:21', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/gm_renaissance_center_wide_main_b.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\nGeneral Motors Company said today that it has returned $140 million to the U.S. Treasury Department for a program that was created in April to help auto suppliers get paid. The program, which once had $5 billion to aid parts suppliers, has continued to shrink. GM was originally allocated $3.5 billion while Chrysler was given [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/k0zElcLpQQs/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'GM pays $140 million to U.S. Treasury for supplier aid program'),
(1040, '2', '2022-11-25 16:27:32', '<img src=\"http://www.rpmgo.com/images2009/saab_badge.jpg\" alt=\"Karma strikes GM as Koenigsegg backs down from Saab purchase\" />\nOuch! Do you feel that? It’s karma coming back around and bitting General Motors right where it hurts the most.\nAfter backing down at the last possible moment from selling German carmaker Opel to Canadian partsmaker Magna and its partner, Sberbank from Russia, Swedish supercarmaker Koenigsegg revealed that it won’t purchase fellow manufacturer Saab from GM.\n“We’re [...]Post published on Rpmgo.comKarma strikes GM as Koenigsegg backs down from Saab purchase\n\n\n\nRelated posts:Koenigsegg wants fewer but more expensive Saab models, takes the brand upmarket  As you all know, ...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AutoUnleashed/~3/qAv22nPGZIk/karma-strikes-gm-as-koenigsegg-backs-down-from-saab-purchase\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Karma strikes GM as Koenigsegg backs down from Saab purchase'),
(1041, '2', '2022-11-25 16:16:59', '<img src=\"http://www.rpmgo.com/images2009/bentley_badge.jpg\" alt=\"Bentley preparing three-door shooting brake and crossover models?\" />\nIt seems that the team at Bentley is quite busy these days, as it has just released the Mulsanne, which will be the base for the replacements of the Brooklands and Azure, is preparing to revamp the Continental lineup, and, according to a new report, may also be researching two new cars, a three-door shooting [...]Post published on Rpmgo.comBentley preparing three-door shooting brake and crossover models?\n\n\n\nRelated posts:Bentley Continental GT ‘TETSU GTR’ tuning by ASI  Japanese tuning company ASI has a record of very...Bentley introduces the Continental GT Speed  Bentley made a p...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AutoUnleashed/~3/UkcWg41suis/bentley-preparing-three-door-shooting-brake-and-crossover-models\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Bentley preparing three-door shooting brake and crossover models?'),
(1042, '2', '2022-11-25 17:12:19', '\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nGeneral Motors announced today that it will build its upcoming Buick Regal in Oshawa, Ontario, rather than in Germany as the company had previously announced. The Regal will join the Chevrolet Camaro and, also in the first quarter of 2011, the Camaro Convertible at the Canadian plant.\n\nThe decision to build the Regal at the Oshawa [...]\n\n\n...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.leftlanenews.com/click.phdo?i=17c6f8f1dbff22914859e5328c3b22a6\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.leftlanenews.com</a><br>', 'GM to build Regal in Oshawa, confirms Camaro Convertible for Q1 2011'),
(1043, '2', '2022-11-25 17:03:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/green.autoblog.com/media/2009/05/audi-a3-tdi-1280-03_opt.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Etc., Europe/EU\n\nAudi A3 TDI - Click above for high-res image gallery\n\nMost likely due to the current economic downturn, most business rentals are getting smaller. According to a new report by rent-a-car company Europcar of the latest rentals in 18 European countries, price is now a determining factor for businesses. Therefore, companies that used to rent relatively large sedans now stick to the \"4-meter\" category, including the Audi A3, Renault Mégane, and Volkswagen Golf. The reasons? A lower rental price, sure, but also better fuel economy. These cars are offered with sm...<br><a href=\"http://green.autoblog.com/2009/11/25/downsizing-businesses-in-europe-shifting-to-smaller-rental-cars/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: green.autoblog.com</a><br>', 'Downsizing: businesses in Europe shifting to smaller rental cars'),
(1044, '2', '2022-11-25 16:56:18', '<img src=\"http://www.automobilesreview.com/uploads/2009/11/Renault-Twingo-Gordini-Renaultsport-thumb.jpg\" alt=\"Renault inveiled the 2010 Twingo Gordini Renaultsport\" />Renault Twingo Gordini Renaultsport is finally unveiled, which marks the official return of the Gordini name in the automobile industry. The fresh pocket rocket from Renault features all the design cues ever associated with the Gordini name, shaped with modern style.\nThe small Twingo Gordini Renaultsport strikes with its unique combination of French blue, white racing [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.automobilesreview.com/auto-news/2010-renault-twingo-gordini-renaultsport/19887/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.automobilesreview.com</a><br>', 'Renault inveiled the 2010 Twingo Gordini Renaultsport'),
