(1116, '2', '2022-11-26 00:53:21', 'Hyundai has confirmed that the rear-drive Genesis Coupe will be built in right-hand drive and will arrive in the UK towards the end of 2010. The coupe is based on the Genesis saloon, which will be built in right-hand drive as well; however, it will not come to the UK. Rather, it will be sold [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/hyundai-genesis-coupe-to-make-its-uk-debut-by-the-end-of-the-year/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Hyundai Genesis Coupe to make its U.K. debut by the end of the year'),
(1117, '2', '2022-11-26 01:02:33', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/nissan_qazana_wide_main_a.jpg\" alt=\"Nissan Qazana\" />\nAccording to insiders at Nissan, the upcoming Qazana SUV is generating a “love it or hate it” reaction. The Qazana, which is due to go on sale in October 2010, is expected to kickoff a new design era for the Japanese automaker.\n“The Nissan brand is going to have a more attractive and emotional appeal in [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/xr-Q2Dz8zS4/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Nissan Qazana generating “love it or hate it” reaction, production model due in Oct. 2010'),
(1118, '2', '2022-11-26 00:30:00', ' We have some good news for all the Mini Diesel fans that crave a more powerful model. A car the combines the elements of the sporty Mini Cooper S and the fuel-efficiency of the Mini Diesel has been spotted in Germany, suggesting that a new Mini Cooper S Diesel is in the works. According to onlookers, the prototype seen here featured a typical...\r\n    \r\n...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/MotorAuthority/~3/vW2YwsDMZmk/1039024_spy-shots-2011-mini-cooper-diesel-s\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Spy Shots: 2011 Mini Cooper Diesel S'),
(1119, '2', '2022-11-26 01:58:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/green.autoblog.com/media/2009/11/2420667909_6eefde8586_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Etc., Green Daily\n\nTurns out, getting off of gasoline might save more than parts of the environment. According to a study published in BMC Physiology, rats exposed to unleaded gasoline fumes for 30 minutes a day for six weeks \"exhibited an increase in lipid peroxidation and a decrease in AChE and superoxide dismutase activities.\" What does that mean? The rats got mad and had \"a higher tendency towards aggressive behaviour as a consequence to gasoline inhalation.\" Basically, gasoline vapors can piss us off.\n\nThe study was conducted by Amal Kinawy of Cairo University, who says that ...<br><a href=\"http://green.autoblog.com/2009/11/25/something-to-be-thankful-for-getting-off-of-gas-might-reduce-ro/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: green.autoblog.com</a><br>', 'Something to be thankful for: getting off of gas might reduce road rage'),
(1120, '2', '2022-11-26 02:16:55', 'All four Opel factories in Germany will remain open under General Motors Co.’s 3.3 billion euro ($4.92 billion) restructuring plan for the European unit. Workers were concerned about GM’s plan to reduce production across Europe by 20-25% (the equivalent of three plants) as part of its reorganization plan.\nActing Opel CEO Nick Reilly has reassured German [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/general-motors-to-keep-open-all-four-of-its-opel-factories-in-germany/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'General Motors to keep open all four of its Opel factories in Germany'),
(1121, '2', '2022-11-26 02:05:09', 'It is expected that for the second year in a row, Porsche Automobil Holding SE will have an annual loss in the billions of euros. Unfortunately, Porsche still hasn’t been able to recover from ex-CEO Wendelin Wiedeking’s failed takeover of Volkswagen AG. Porsche’s debt had mounted as the automotive markets collapsed.\nAs a result, Porsche had [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/porsche-heading-for-a-second-consecutive-annual-loss/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Porsche heading for a second consecutive annual loss'),
