(1131, '2', '2022-11-26 08:10:05', '<img src=\"http://www.rpmgo.com/images2009/mazda_3.jpg\" alt=\"Mazda thinking about new compact crossover CX-3\" />\nWhile Mazda’s SUVs, the CX-7 and CX-9, haven’t really blown everyone away, it seems that the Japanese carmaker is confident that the market is ripe and is preparing, reportedly, to unveil a brand new compact crossover, dubbed the CX-3.\nThe new model, which might be basing itself on the Mazda 3, will take full advantage of [...]Post published on Rpmgo.comMazda thinking about new compact crossover CX-3\n\n\n\nRelated posts:Updated Mazda Axela debuts in Japan  The new Mazda Axela (or the Mazda 3 as...Mazda CX-9 makes European debut at Moscow  After winning North America’s 2008 truck of...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AutoUnleashed/~3/hbkBRuFb0ss/mazda-thinking-about-new-compact-crossover-cx-3\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Mazda thinking about new compact crossover CX-3');
