(1366, '2', '2022-11-30 07:07:33', '\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nJust days ahead of the Los Angeles International Auto Show, Ford has taken the wraps off of the all-new powertrain for the 2011 Ford Mustang in V6 trim. The new Mustang features changes inside and out, but most importantly a new 3.7-liter V6 capable of 305 horsepower and 30 mpg highway. \n  \n Ford [...]\n\n\n...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.leftlanenews.com/click.phdo?i=67e1df5addbb6a8cfbe6348d1597ea99\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.leftlanenews.com</a><br>', '2011 Mustang V6 unveiled before LA Auto Show'),
(1367, '2', '2022-11-30 07:05:16', '<img src=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/cruzeext-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"2011 Chevrolet Cruze\" />\nPictured above is the production version of the all-new Chevy Cruze. This past Fall we have sampled from Chevy the Camaro RS and Equinox, both great vehicles that we would happily recommend to anyone. But the real test for Chevy comes with the Cruze, as the outgoing Cobalt, although a strong seller, failed to convince [...]...<br><a href=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/chevy-cruze-unveiled/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: thegarageblog.com</a><br>', 'Chevy Cruze Unveiled'),
(1368, '2', '2022-11-30 07:11:15', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/2011_ford_mustang_v6_press_images_main.jpg\" alt=\"2011_ford_mustang_v6_press_images_main\" />\nIf you currently own a 2010 Ford Mustang V6 model, you are about to be incredibly frustrated. However, if you’re one of those die-hard Mustang fans that has been waiting for Ford to offer a V6 Mustang that would stand up tough against the 304-hp 2010 Chevrolet Camaro V6, you’re in for a big treat [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/GankbEKsKno/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2009 LA Preview: 2011 Ford Mustang V6 gets 305-hp 3.7L V6'),
(1369, '2', '2022-11-30 06:43:35', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/2011_chevrolet_cruze_press_images_main.jpg\" alt=\"2011 Chevrolet Cruze\" />\nThe U.S.-spec Chevrolet Cruze has been unveiled prior to its world debut at the 2009 LA Auto Show on Dec. 2. The 2010 Chevrolet Cruze compact sedan, which will replace the Chevy Cobalt, will go on sale in the third quarter of 2010 and will be built at GM’s Lordstown Ohio assembly plant.\nThe five-door, front-wheel-drive [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/_pZnHLXR61c/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2009 LA Preview: 2011 Chevrolet Cruze unveiled for the U.S. market'),
(1370, '2', '2022-11-30 08:03:12', '<img src=\"http://www.rpmgo.com/images2009/volvo_geely.jpg\" alt=\"Volvo getting closer to Geely after Chinese company secures intellectual rights from Ford\" />\nWhile last week was almost all about Saab and the failed Koenigsegg - GM deal which left the Swedish brand once again without no future owner, things weren’t standing still for fellow carmaker Volvo.\nA new report indicates that the Chinese officials from Geely, the preferred bidder for the Scandinavian brand, are getting closer to buying [...]Post published on Rpmgo.comVolvo getting closer to Geely after Chinese company secures intellectual rights from Ford\n\n\n\nRelated posts:New Volvo models will appear if Geely buys it from Ford  According to recent sources close to the Chinese carmaker...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AutoUnleashed/~3/0JmHIVyiPNw/volvo-getting-closer-to-geely-after-chinese-company-secures-intellectual-rights-from-ford\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Volvo getting closer to Geely after Chinese company secures intellectual rights from Ford');
