(1437, '2', '2022-11-30 17:54:18', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/toyota_hybrid_x_concept_wide_main.jpg\" alt=\"Toyota Hybrid X Concept\" />\nToyota recently confirmed that it will use the Prius name on more hybrid models in its U.S. lineup. It said that the Prius name would be attached to “a family of models” using similar hybrid powertrains. According to a report by AutoExpress, a new crossover/SUV hybrid will be the first model in a new range [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/8NxdIuWOoQY/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Report: Toyota Crossover hybrid will be next to wear Prius badge'),
(1438, '2', '2022-11-30 17:58:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/www.autoblog.com/media/2009/11/2011chevyvolt_qd_000_opt.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Hybrid, Hatchback, Chevrolet, GM, Electric, Quick Spin\r\n2011 Chevrolet Volt - Click above for high-res image gallery\r\n\r\nThree years ago this December we first walked into a Manhattan conference room for a background briefing on a new concept being developed by General Motors for the upcoming Detroit Auto Show. Earlier that year, the release of a documentary called Who Killed the Electric Car made the then largest automaker in the world the subject of some well deserved criticism for its handling of the end of the EV1 program. The movie and announcement of the all-electric Tesla Ro...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogsinc/autoblog/~3/Jl3gqoUwugs/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Quick Spin: 2011 Chevrolet Volt charges toward production'),
