(2224, '3', '2022-12-06 19:12:55', '<img src=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/nasa25daybreak-29-500x332.jpg\" alt=\"nasa25daybreak (29)\" />\nDaybreak came bright and sunny today at the 25 Hours of Thunderhill following a very cold night. At least it wasn’t raining, which means that the folks at Head-On Photos were able to grab some incredible photos of overnight and early morning action.\nAnother huge gallery after the break.\n\nRelated PostGoing Iron Man in the longest race [...]...<br><a href=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/gallery-overnight-and-daybreak-at-2009-nasa-25-hours-of-thunderhill/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: thegarageblog.com</a><br>', 'Gallery: Overnight and daybreak at 2009 NASA 25 Hours of Thunderhill'),
(2225, '3', '2022-12-06 18:45:36', '<img src=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/14543_215745361753_102793526753_4117024_2109751_n-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"14543_215745361753_102793526753_4117024_2109751_n\" />\nThe 25 Hours of Thunderhill has been an interesting event over the years in that the occasional full on pro team show up with a beast of a machine that some expect to sweep the race. This doesn’t always happen though, as the big guns are usually there to test a new package and make [...]...<br><a href=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/bmc-tool-racing-provides-a-6-hour-video-report-from-25-hours-of-thunderhill/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: thegarageblog.com</a><br>', 'BMC Tool Racing provides a 6 hour video report from 25 Hours of Thunderhill'),
(2226, '3', '2022-12-06 18:41:31', 'This is the third recall related to the Fiat Grande Punto’s steering column that had been announced since Fiat Group Automobiles discovered the defect. The recall of 500,000 units is the largest of the three and it affects Fiat’s top-selling car in Europe and worldwide – the Grande Punto and Grande Punto Abarth built in [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/fiat-recalling-500000-units-of-the-grande-punto/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Fiat recalling 500,000 units of the Grande Punto'),
(2227, '3', '2022-12-06 19:21:47', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/buick_gmc_cadillac_dealership.jpg\" alt=\"LaFontaine Buick-Pontiac-GMC-Cadillac Dealership, Michigan\" />\nGM has announced that it is ready to take action on a comprehensive plan that resolves concerns raised by dealers regarding GM’s dealer network restructuring activities.\n“GM will begin to implement this plan in mid-January provided that legislation related to GM’s dealer restructuring does not move forward,” the company said in a statement. “GM’s plan offers [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/cbhoB403N4A/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'GM releases plan to address dealer concerns'),
(2228, '3', '2022-12-06 19:09:33', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2010_nissan_qashqai_images_main.jpg\" alt=\"2010 Nissan Qashqai\" />\nThe Nissan Qashqai, which has been on sale in Europe since March 2007, has been totally redesigned for the 2010 model year. The new redesigned model won’t hit dealerships until spring 2010, but Nissan says that it expects it 500,000th delivery to take place later this month.\nNew for 2010, the Qashqai gets a redesigned front-end, [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/7wcu0Rd1zSE/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2010 Nissan Qashqai revealed, get fuel-efficent Pure Drive variant'),
(2229, '3', '2022-12-06 19:32:56', 'At the Los Angeles Auto Show, Mazda is showing three tuned concepts based on the small Mazda2. First one is called Mazda 2Evil Special Concept and is inspired by the weekend track car, which functions equally well as an urban commuter. \nThe body has been modified to show a more aggressive front spoiler and a [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.globalmotors.net/los-angeles-2009-customized-mazda2-concepts/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.globalmotors.net</a><br>', 'Los Angeles 2009: Customized Mazda2 Concepts'),
(2230, '3', '2022-12-06 19:57:57', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/mercedes_benz_slr_era_end_main.jpg\" alt=\"Mercedes-Benz SLR Family Group Picture\" />\nMercedes-Benz announced today that it is building the last examples of the SLR Stirling Moss as it prepares to end the era of the SLR supercars from Mercedes-Benz and McLaren. The two started in 2004 to continue the story of the legendary SLR racing sports cars of the 1950s.\nFive variants later – two coupes, two [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/0M-sPAohjN8/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Mercedes-Benz ends SLR era with last examples of SLR Stirling Moss'),
(2231, '3', '2022-12-06 19:40:32', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/henrik_fisker_karma_live.jpg\" alt=\"Fisker Karma\" />\nFisker Automotive has been going through a lot of changing since it was founded in August 2007 by Henrik Fisker. At the 2009 LA Auto Show, Fisker outlined those changes during a press conference and one point that stood out the most is that the deliveries of company’s Karma plug-in hybrid sedan have been delayed. [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/TOQ1LPWBeCY/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2009 LA: Fisker Karma delayed until 3rd quarter of 2010'),
(2232, '3', '2022-12-06 21:14:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/green.autoblog.com/media/2009/12/091202_ar_giulietta01-copy.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Geneva Motor Show, Alfa Romeo\nAlfa Romeo Giulietta - click above for high res image gallery\n\nThe beauty of reporting on new Alfa Romeo models from North America is that, after years of false promises, we may now finally be on the verge of actually getting some of them over here again. The new Alfa Romeo Giulietta will be replacing the outgoing 147 some time after it debuts at the Geneva Motor Show next March. If Fiat does ultimately decide to offer the brand through its Chrysler alliance, this will probably one of the models. The sporty five-door hatch will have five engines avail...<br><a href=\"http://green.autoblog.com/2009/12/06/new-alfa-romeo-giulietta-to-get-turbocharged-engine-range-with-s/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: green.autoblog.com</a><br>', 'New Alfa Romeo Giulietta to get turbocharged engine range with start/stop'),
(2233, '3', '2022-12-06 20:51:16', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2009_la_auto_show_collection.jpg\" alt=\"2009 LA Auto Show Collection\" />\nThe curtains on our live coverage of the 2009 LA Auto Show closed on Thursday. We decided to put together a little list of the most significant debuts that were revealed in Los Angeles and some you should definitely plan on checking out if you’ll be heading down to the show this week.\nThanks for joining [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/KaZXAHz6gvI/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2009 LA Auto Show: A look back at the most significant debuts of the show'),
