(2329, '3', '2022-12-08 12:30:21', '<img src=\"http://www.wired.com/images_blogs/autopia/2009/12/image001.jpg\" alt=\"image001\" />\nDebuting at the Geneva Auto Show in March is an all-new four-passenger, electric luxury vehicle featuring hand stitched seats, a double wishbone suspension and even an on-board refrigerator. It’s called the Garia and it’s not a bad deal for $17,499 — unless you consider that it’s a golf cart.\nTo be perfectly accurate, it’s a golf [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.wired.com/~r/wiredautopia/~3/Ndd1tHN2xwc/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.wired.com</a><br>', 'Garia Brings All-Electric Luxury To The Links'),
(2330, '3', '2022-12-08 05:11:12', '<img src=\"http://www.wired.com/images_blogs/autopia/2009/12/ss2-and-vms-eve-preview8-660x402.jpg\" alt=\"SpaceShip2- Unveils in Mojave,CA\" />\nOn a cold and windy night at the Mojave Air and Space Port, the VSS Enterprise was unveiled to the public tonight. Attached to its mother ship, the vehicle better known as SpaceShipTwo is expected to be the first commercial spacecraft when it enters service with Virgin Galactic.\nSpaceShipTwo was built by Scaled Composites under the [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.wired.com/~r/wiredautopia/~3/HrjsJa8KuDI/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.wired.com</a><br>', 'SpaceShipTwo Christened VSS Enterprise'),
(2331, '3', '2022-12-07 23:35:26', '<img src=\"http://www.wired.com/images_blogs/autopia/2009/12/ss2-and-vms-eve3-660x423.jpg\" alt=\"SS2 and VMS Eve in hangar 3\" />\nAfter more than five years of waiting, Virgin Galactic’s SpaceShipTwo is ready to be unveiled to the public tonight at a ceremony in the Mojave desert. Following on the success of SpaceShipOne in 2004, the six passenger SpaceShipTwo already has a backlog of more than 300 passengers who are waiting for their ride into space.\nVirgin [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.wired.com/~r/wiredautopia/~3/AjJz_911rQM/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.wired.com</a><br>', 'Virgin Galactic Ready To Unveil SpaceShipTwo'),
(2332, '3', '2022-12-07 21:03:28', '<img src=\"http://www.wired.com/images_blogs/autopia/2009/12/volkswagen_up_lite_01.jpg\" alt=\"volkswagen_up_lite_01\" />\nVolkswagen keeps teasing us with diesel hybrids, and its latest flirtation is a sweet ultralight, ultra-aerodynamic diesel-electric that gets 70 mpg on the highway.\nVW rolled into the Los Angeles Auto Show with the Up! Lite (and no, we don’t know why there’s an exclamation point in the name). The super-slick hatchback is the latest in [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.wired.com/~r/wiredautopia/~3/10ymkeAh-Iw/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.wired.com</a><br>', 'Sweet VW Diesel Hybrid Gets 70 MPG'),
