(2404, '3', '2022-12-09 23:22:02', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/BlogBanner.jpg\" alt=\"BlogBanner\" />\n+ We compare four categories of tires able to deal with winter and come up with some surprising results. [Car and Driver]\n+ Tested: The 2010 Kia Forte EX sedan is a formidable contender in the compact class.  [Car and Driver]\n+ Somehow, Porsche has built a better Boxster. Meet the 2010 Boxster SPyder. [Car and Driver]\n\n+ [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:Daily Downshift: December 1, 2009Daily Downshift: December 2, 2009Daily Downshift: December 4, 2009...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/hhDTXDqXFmc/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Daily Downshift: December 9, 2009'),
(2405, '3', '2022-12-09 19:51:48', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2010-Porsche-911-Turbo-coupe-placement-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"2010 Porsche 911 Turbo coupe\" />\nWhale Done: After 35 years and six generations of turbos, Porsche still finds much to improve. Don’t let the mildly revised looks fool you.\nPorsche introduced the 911 Turbo 35 years ago in Europe, shortly after the first fuel crisis and in the thick of a worldwide crackdown on automotive smog emissions. The ­company expected to [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2010 Porsche 911 Turbo – First Drive Review2010 Porsche 911 Turbo – Official Photos and Info10Best Test Notes: 2010 Porsche 911...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/CpmKh9Av-8A/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2010 Porsche 911 Turbo – Second Drive'),
(2406, '3', '2022-12-09 18:26:28', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2009_volkswagen_jetta_tdi_1_cd_gallery-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"2009_volkswagen_jetta_tdi_1_cd_gallery\" />\n31,011 miles/38 observed mpg.\nAn extra-cold winter left us grateful for fast-heating seats, especially since the Jetta’s diesel takes a while to provide warm air from the heater on frigid mornings. Highways have been the preferred habitat for this German sedan, where even a diminutive 14.5-gallon tank delivers 500-mile intervals between fuel stops. Around town, a [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2009 Volkswagen Jetta TDI – Short Take Road TestGreen and Kinda Mean: We Race in the Volkswagen Jetta TDI Cup – Sport2009 Volkswagen Touareg TDI – Short Take Road Test...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/hV_tZS7H7WY/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2009 Volkswagen Jetta TDI – Long-Term Road Test Update'),
(2407, '3', '2022-12-09 18:22:41', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2010-Kia-Forte-EX-Sedan-3-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"2010-Kia-Forte-EX-Sedan-3\" />\nKia’s continuing crescendo gives us the formidable Forte.\nKia’s current and upcoming product catalog suggests a naming strategy solely inspired by someone’s old music dictionary. Both the Rondo and the upcoming Cadenza draw their names from musical terminology—as does parent Hyundai’s Sonata—and now we have the Forte, christened with an Italian word that directs performers to [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2010 Kia Forte SX – Short Take Road Test10Best Test Notes: 2010 Kia Forte / Kia Forte Koup – Cheaper Can be Better2010 Kia Forte Koup SX – Short Take Road Test...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/p2bDPGLR-gs/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2010 Kia Forte EX – Short Take Road Test'),
(2408, '3', '2022-12-09 17:38:52', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Fantasy-Showroom-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"Fantasy-Showroom\" />\nThink you’re up on car-buying trends? Then try your hand at Fantasy Showroom, a new online game that rewards players for picking the cars and trucks that are successful in the real world of auto sales. Fantasy Showroom was created by Jumpstart Automotive Group, of which Car and Driver is a part.\nSimilar to fantasy sports [...]\n\n\nNo related posts....<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/_OEu0i9MvUI/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Fantasy Showroom: Like Fantasy Football for Gearheads'),
(2409, '3', '2022-12-09 17:32:57', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2010-nissan-versa-hatchback-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"2010-nissan-versa-hatchback\" />\nStill cheap, simple, and sensible, the littlest Nissan gets some minor enhancements for 2010.\nWHAT IS IT? \n\nNissan’s least-expensive car and, in sedan form, one of the least-expensive cars you can buy, period. And it’s not totally awful. For 2010, the Nissan Versa includes a few barely noticeable enhancements (new grille, wheels, and wheel covers) on [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2009 Nissan Versa 1.6 Sedan – Short Take Road Test2010 Nissan Versa 1.8 SL Hatchback – Quick Spin2009 Nissan Versa Sedan and Hatchback – Review...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/W2cGNkOC4SE/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2010 Nissan Versa 1.8 SL Hatchback – Short Take Road Test'),
(2410, '3', '2022-12-09 17:32:14', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2010-Hyundai-Tucson-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"2010-Hyundai-Tucson\" />\nThe stylish new 2010 Hyundai Tucson will start at $19,790 in GLS trim with front-wheel drive and a six-speed manual transmission. Standard equipment in GLS guise is generous and includes six airbags, iPod connectivity, hill-start and downhill-braking assist, air conditioning, and more. The GLS with automatic transmission is $20,790.\nMoving up to the Popular Equipment package [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2010 Hyundai Tucson – Auto Shows2010 Hyundai Tucson – Auto Shows2010 Audi Q7 Starts at $47,725...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/Fk_K7TprV5w/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2010 Hyundai Tucson Starts at $19,790'),
(2411, '3', '2022-12-09 17:05:23', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Winterkorn-and-Suzuki-sign-agreement-440x292.jpg\" alt=\"Martin Winterkorn, Chairman of the Board of Management of Volkswagen AG, and Osamu Suzuki, CEO Suzuki \" />With the ink still drying on its check for a 49.9-percent stake of Porsche, Volkswagen has entered into an agreement with Suzuki Motor Corporation. In what’s being called a “long-term strategic partnership,” the German giant will work together with the Japanese automaker on smaller vehicles and those aimed at emerging markets. The two companies claim [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2009 Volkswagen Jetta TDI – Long-Term Road Test UpdateWill the Next Suzuki Swift Come to the U.S.?Suzuki Samurai Fights Back?...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/L_ThlQLl4S4/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Suzuki and Volkswagen Shake Hands on “Long-Term Strategic Partnership”'),
(2412, '3', '2022-12-09 16:05:28', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/11/2009-Nissan-370Z-placement-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"2009 Nissan 370Z\" />\n6858 miles/20 observed mpg.\nAs our reigning champion in the “sub-$40K sports-car” class, the 370Z was a shoo-in for a long-term test. This one entered our fleet in Touring guise in April. We like the slick, SynchroRev Match transmission feature (part of the $3000 Sport package), as well as the balanced handling and straight-line thrust. But [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2010 Nissan 370Z Touring Roadster – Short Take Road Test2009 Honda Pilot Touring 4WD – Long-Term Road Test Update2009 Nissan 370Z – Road Test...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/YQV3KPZdERI/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2009 Nissan 370Z Touring – Long-Term Road Test Update'),
(2413, '3', '2022-12-09 16:04:54', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/VW-Buys-Stake-in-Porsche-220x134.jpg\" alt=\"VW-Buys-Stake-in-Porsche\" />The VW/Porsche drama is over—and the result is hardly a merger. VW chief Martin Winterkorn and his CFO Hans Dieter Pötsch have taken over the same positions at Porsche Automobil Holding. On December 7, Volkswagen bought 49.9 percent of Porsche  for €3.9 billion (over $5.7 billion). Porsche desperately needs the cash to pay off debts [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:Volkswagen Will Buy $4.7B Stake in Porsche2010 Porsche Cayenne GTS Porsche Design Edition 3 – Car NewsIs Porsche Really Planning the 2010 Porsche Roxster / Baby Cayenne SUV?...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/V4j7RXd9sjI/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Volkswagen Buys 49.9 Percent Stake in Porsche'),
