(2605, '3', '2022-12-10 21:16:00', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2010-Dodge-Viper-ACR-X-4-2-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"2010 Dodge Viper SRT10 ACR-X.\" />\nThe third special-edition 2010 Viper leaves public roads behind.\nDodge has recently announced that 2010 will be the last year of production for the current Viper, and that it will be celebrating with a series of limited-edition models. Following the appearance-only ACR Voodoo Edition and ACR 1:33 Edition—the latter named for the unofficial Laguna Seca lap [...]\n\n\nNo related posts....<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/CqCSSkXvsz8/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2010 Dodge Viper ACR-X – Car News'),
(2606, '3', '2022-12-10 20:06:09', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2011-Dodge-Charger-2-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"2011-Dodge-Charger-2\" />\nThe next-gen Charger is caught in the wild.\nAs Chrysler continues to struggle in the absence of new product, it’s refreshing to finally get a glimpse of the next-generation Dodge Charger, which can’t get here soon enough. Although it’s covered in camouflage, we’re able to see some new cues that appear to have been influenced by [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2009 Dodge Charger / Charger SRT8 – Review2008 Pontiac G8 GT vs. 2008 Dodge Charger R/T2011 Volkswagen Jetta – Spied...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/RW7rz3QwqI0/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2011 Dodge Charger – Spied'),
(2607, '3', '2022-12-10 20:56:19', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/roush_427r_mustang_main_a.jpg\" alt=\"ROUSH 2010 427R Mustang\" />\nWhile it isn’t giving away too many details, Roush said yesterday that it is introducing a new in-house lifestyle club next year that will charge Roush owners and members $35 a year. The tuner says that there are about 16,000 of its vehicles out on the U.S. roads, which could lead to upward of $500,000 [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/zUYuQErmQF0/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Roush to introduce new high-performance ‘lifestyle club’ next year'),
(2608, '3', '2022-12-10 20:42:40', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2010_dodge_ram_2500.jpg\" alt=\"2010 Ram 2500 Power Wagon\" />\nThe editors of Motor Trend have chosen the 2010 Ram 2500/3500 Heavy Duty pickups their 2010 Truck of the Year.\n“The 2010 Ram Heavy Duty absolutely nailed the award in terms of our criteria, from the attractive exterior styling, to the plush and quiet cabins, to the tough and capable powertrains, especially the impressive Cummins diesel, [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/JR4GrkhQNck/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2010 Ram Heavy Duty named Motor Trend’s 2010 Truck of the Year'),
(2609, '3', '2022-12-10 20:28:25', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/bmw_m1_hommage_concept_main_wide.jpg\" alt=\"BMW M1 Hommage Concept\" />\nThe last time we heard anything about the M1 Hommage Concept it was reported that BMW is working on a green supercar based on the model for 2012. Since then, BMW has shown its Vision EfficientDynamics Concept, which has confused us as to what exactly BMW plans on doing with the M1 Hommage Concept.\nAccording to [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/EnnGGUiSiQg/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Renewed BMW M1 Hommage Concept coming to Dubai Motor Show'),
(2610, '3', '2022-12-10 19:59:18', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2010_dodge_viper_srt10_acr_x_images_main.jpg\" alt=\"2010 Dodge Viper SRT10 ACR-X\" />\nThere is no doubt that the last 500 units of the Dodge Viper will be extremely special before it is replaced by a new supercar in 2010. Dodge today unveiled a new special-edition model of its 2010 Viper SRT10 – the 2010 Dodge Viper SRT10 ACR-X. The special-edition model is a non-street legal model ready to make [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/O5jGGivrxbQ/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2010 Dodge Viper SRT10 ACR-X makes 640-hp, only for the track'),
(2611, '3', '2022-12-10 19:59:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/green.autoblog.com/media/2009/12/lotus-omnivore-engine-copy.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Technology, LotusLast March at the Geneva Motor Show, Lotus announced its new Omnivore research engine. The Omnivore is a two-stroke direct-injected engine designed to take advantage of the latest in electronic engine management and run on just about any liquid fuel (hence the name). In the time since the initial announcement, the boffins at Lotus Engineering have been exercising their creation on the dyno stand to evaluate its performance. \r\n\r\nThe single-cylinder engine uses an air-assisted direct injection system. A movable \"puck\" in the top of the cylinder head allows the compr...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogsinc/autoblog/~3/OFjYYuMItnc/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Lotus: Omnivore engine is 10% more efficient with more to come'),
(2612, '3', '2022-12-12 20:35:59', '<img src=\"http://carphotos.cardomain.com/ride_images/2/3178/1361/20443180024_large.jpg\" alt=\"Saab\" />Saab has been a hot potato for GM as of late. The company started a deal to sell the brand to a Swedish sports car manufacturer but it fell apart in the late innings, then there was discussion with the Swedish government that ultimately went nowhere, and now there is talk the Chinese may be [...]...<br><a href=\"http://blog.cardomain.com/2009/12/10/saab-sale-news-chinese-may-buy-some-assets-others-interested-in-whole-company/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: blog.cardomain.com</a><br>', 'Saab sale news: Chinese may buy some assets, others interested in whole company'),
(2613, '3', '2022-12-10 20:28:14', '<img src=\"http://carphotos.cardomain.com/ride_images/4/203/4522/38007260580_large.jpg\" alt=\"1963 Chevrolet Greenbrier\" />A fairly straightforward find today – a black-plate California Greenbrier with 50k on the clock for $13,750. From the seller’s description:\n`963 Corvair”Greenbrier” deluxe sport van; top-of-the line model; deluxe interior (completely correct) with original rubber mats; correct body cloth and original paneling; roll-down deluxe windows; 50,000 rust-free So. Cal miles; recent re-build to auto trans [...]...<br><a href=\"http://blog.cardomain.com/2009/12/10/hemmings-find-of-the-day-%e2%80%93-1963-chevrolet-greenbrier/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: blog.cardomain.com</a><br>', 'Hemmings Find of the Day – 1963 Chevrolet Greenbrier'),
(2614, '3', '2022-12-10 21:24:17', '\nWe’re always looking for new ways to kill time between trips to the water cooler here at Autopia, and this video delivers.\nIt’s a cool stop-motion homage to Peter Gabriel’s Sledgehammer video featuring a self-assembling Suzuki GSX-R with a parade of garage tools and man-toys. The five-minute video took roughly 30 hours of god-like patience of [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.wired.com/~r/wiredautopia/~3/qkDjBkn_bk0/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.wired.com</a><br>', 'Cool Video: Suzuki Motorcycle Assembles Itself'),
(2615, '3', '2022-12-12 22:00:00', '<img src=\"http://img.worldcarfans.com/2009/12/23476.tn.jpg\" alt=\"http://img.worldcarfans.com/2009/12/23476.tn.jpg\" /> From 2014 the US will very much build its own next-generation Mercedes-Benz C-Class units, according to a statement from Daimler.\r\n \r\n...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.worldcarfans.com/~r/worldcarfans/Jxfz/~3/2GpVkMzzcOg/daimler-confirms-mercedes-c-class-us-production-in-2014\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.worldcarfans.com</a><br>', ' Daimler Confirms Mercedes C-Class U.S. Production in 2014'),
(2616, '3', '2022-12-10 23:00:19', '\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nUnconfirmed reports are suggesting that the “Zoom-Zoom” automaker may have a new high-tech 4-cylinder engine, code named “Sky-G” in the works for their 2011 Miata. Reports put the potential mileage as high as 70 miles per gallon.\n\nAccording to InsideLine, the naturally aspirated 1.3-liter 4-cylinder engine that was first introduced at the 2009 Tokyo Auto Show [...]\n\n\n...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.leftlanenews.com/click.phdo?i=b9b16f108272d54f86d31bc5416e7451\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.leftlanenews.com</a><br>', 'Report: 2011 Mazda Miata to be rated at up to 70 mpg'),
(2617, '3', '2022-12-10 22:24:36', '\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDetroit’s Big Three automakers are voicing concern over Japan’s version of the cash for clunkers program, which declares virtually all imported vehicles ineligible for government rebates. The Big Three have taken their concerns to the U.S. Government in a call for action.\n\nJapan has recently launched its own version of the cash for clunkers program in [...]\n\n\n...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.leftlanenews.com/click.phdo?i=b910578d402ee9ce75738e0918bc7519\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.leftlanenews.com</a><br>', 'Japanese cash for clunkers program draws criticism');
