(2624, '3', '2022-12-10 23:48:11', '<img src=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/wp-content/uploads/DG010_048VP-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"2010 Dodge Viper SRT10 ACR-X.\" />\nAfter the recent upgrades to the undead Viper SRT10 ACR recently, is it even possible for the snake to get more hard core? Sure it is, just let Ralph Gilles and his boys loose with a pipe bender and a mig welder!\nThat’s right, a pipe bender! \nObviously Gilles is a huge gearhead and has been [...]...<br><a href=\"http://thegarageblog.com/garage/viper-gets-even-more-hardcore-with-introduction-of-acr-x-and-the-dodge-viper-cup/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: thegarageblog.com</a><br>', 'Viper gets even more hardcore with introduction of ACR-X and the Dodge Viper Cup'),
(2625, '3', '2022-12-11 01:27:42', 'The Italian government will extend its incentive scheme to encourage people to buy less-polluting cars and appliances, Industry Minister Claudio Scajola told reporters in Brussels on Monday. Existing incentives had initially been due to end on Dec. 31 but Scajola said that they have come up with a measure that will allow the incentives to [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/italy-to-extend-incentives-for-people-to-buy-less-polluting-cars/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Italy to extend incentives for people to buy less-polluting cars'),
(2626, '3', '2022-12-11 01:14:53', 'Instead of retiring at the end of the year as had been announced, Bill Parfitt, chairman and managing director of General Motors Co.’s Vauxhall division, will stay on as the company’s chairman.\nLast November, 62-year-old Parfitt said that he would retire and retain a non-executive role as chairman. Parfitt’s plans have changed and he will now [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/vauxhall-chairman-postpones-his-retirement/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Vauxhall chairman postpones his retirement'),
(2627, '3', '2022-12-13 00:09:48', 'There’s no stopping MINI’s Coupé and Roadster “twins” from hitting UK and European dealers in the beginning of 2011, with US sales starting immediately after. MINI is fast-tracking the design and development of the cars. We’ve seen them in Frankfurt and LA but so far, design tweaks have been made. Engineering is underway. According to [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/minis-coupe-and-roadster-could-hit-the-streets-by-early-2011/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Mini’s Coupe and Roadster could hit the streets by early 2011'),
(2628, '3', '2022-12-12 23:51:48', 'Kia is believed to enter the luxury sports sedan segment with this car referred to only as K9. So far, only speculations have come out and if it were not for a reader who submitted this picture, we won’t have an idea what it looks like.\nReportedly, Kia’s chief designer Peter Schreyer showed this sketch at [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/leaked-kia-k9-luxury-sedan-teaser-sketch/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Leaked: Kia K9 luxury sedan teaser sketch'),
(2629, '3', '2022-12-10 23:37:31', 'Pricing for Nissan’s 2010 Rogue S Krom Edition, which is now available at US dealerships nationwide, ranges from $24,740 for the front-wheel-drive model to $25,940 for the all-wheel drive one (inclusive of $800 destination charge). \n Buyers can choose from three exterior colors (Venom Red, Wicked Black and Gotham Gray) available for the Rogue S [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/2010-nissan-rogue-s-krom-edition-pricing-announced/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', '2010 Nissan Rogue S Krom Edition pricing announced'),
(2630, '3', '2022-12-10 23:22:01', 'General Motors Co. has to decide if it will sell its Saab unit this week or else, it will be “tough to complete a deal,” according to Joran Hagglund, state secretary at Sweden’s Enterprise Ministry, who spoke to the daily Svenska Dagbladet.\nAt the start of December, GM said that it would be looking at offers [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/report-gm-has-to-decide-this-week-to-sell-or-not-its-saab-brand/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Report: GM has to decide this week to sell or not its Saab brand'),
(2631, '3', '2022-12-10 22:46:43', 'No official announcements have been released by Aston Martin with regards to its plan to upgrade the V8 Vantage for model year 2010 however, according to a source who spoke with Car Magazine, the refreshed series is already available for orders.\nExpect the first models of model year 2010 Vantage V8 to start to be delivered [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/aston-martin-preparing-new-personalisation-options-for-the-v8-vantage/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Aston Martin preparing new personalisation options for the V8 Vantage'),
(2632, '3', '2022-12-10 22:31:28', 'Under a U.S. Labor Department proposal, Ford Motor Co. would be allowed to transfer company securities to a voluntary employee beneficiary association (VEBA) trust to fund a new health plan for company retirees.\nIn a statement released very recently, the department said that the plan is expected to cover more than 285,000 retirees and their dependents, [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/ford-to-fund-a-new-health-plan-for-company-retirees/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Ford to fund a new health plan for company retirees'),
(2633, '3', '2022-12-10 22:06:40', 'For the month of November in Canada, Ford Motor Co. and Toyota Motor Corp. both beat General Motors Co. in terms of new-vehicle sales.\nBut when you consider the sales since the beginning of the year, GM still holds on to the topselling position. GM isn’t the type to be complacent though as it’s to be [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/ford-and-toyota-pass-gm-in-canadian-new-vehicle-sales/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Ford and Toyota pass GM in Canadian new-vehicle sales'),
(2634, '3', '2022-12-10 21:43:35', 'The management shakeup at General Motors Co. continues. Brent Dewar has only headed the Chevrolet division since July but already, he is being replaced by James Campbell.\nBefore handling responsibility for GM’s fleet and commercial unit, Campbell held various positions in field sales, retail incentives, marketing and customer relationship management. Dewar will work with Campbell, who [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/brent-dewar-preparing-to-leave-general-motors/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Brent Dewar preparing to leave General Motors'),
(2635, '3', '2022-12-11 00:09:03', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/BlogBanner.jpg\" alt=\"BlogBanner\" />\n+ Spy photographers caught a camo-clad next-gen Dodge Charger test mule on the street. These shots have us looking forward to seeing the final product. [Car and Driver]\n+ The question has been raised more than once—can the R8 and 911 live under the same roof with the same parents? Audi’s head of global sales and [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:Daily Downshift: December 2, 2009Daily Downshift: December 4, 2009Daily Downshift: December 7, 2009...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/S1qD7DV0uyQ/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Daily Downshift: December 12, 2009'),
(2636, '3', '2022-12-10 22:50:38', '\nOn Tuesday, we posted an audio recording of a mystery car’s exhaust note. To hear it again, click play above. Three of you guessed correctly. It was one of BMW’s new M SUVs, specifically the 2010 BMW X5 M.\nLike it? Download the MP3 and quiz your friends, make your own ringtone, or just lull yourself [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:Name That Exhaust Note, Episode 8: Audi S8Name That Exhaust Note, Episode 2: Maserati QuattroporteName That Exhaust Note, Episode 15: Ferrari F430...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/Jj2Tmbyd4iU/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Name That Exhaust Note, Episode 18: 2010 BMW X5 M'),
(2637, '3', '2022-12-10 22:33:42', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2011-aptera-2e-103-place-440x268.jpg\" alt=\"2011 Aptera 2e\" />\nBigger, safer, and just as radical, the Aptera 2e continues evolving as it inches closer to (probably) launching.\nProving that evolution never stops, even among things that appear to be rather highly evolved already, is the upcoming 2011 Aptera 2e. The space-age three-wheeler may have been delayed “to align with financing realities,” but while Aptera’s suits [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2010 Aptera 2e – First Drive ReviewAptera 2e Electric Car Production and Pricing Announced – Car News2011 Chevrolet Volt: Teaser Images Show Little of Concept’s Styling Will Transfer to Reality...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/38e9j4KoC8s/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2011 Aptera 2e – Official Images'),
(2638, '3', '2022-12-10 21:31:15', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Mugen-Honda-CR-Z-440x238.jpg\" alt=\"Mugen Honda CR-Z\" />\nThe same Japanese fellow who sent the leaked CR-Z brochure shots to Temple of VTEC has now passed along an image of a CR-Z with Mugen accessories.\nWe here at Kaandodoraiba speak very little Japanese, so we’ll let the photo do the talking. There’s a silly rear wing, an aggressive (for a hybrid) front fascia with [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2010 Honda Accord Sedan with Mugen Accessories – Auto ShowsHonda to Import European Two-Door Civic Type R to JapanLeaked: Production Honda CR-Z Pics and Specs Hit the Intertwined Webs...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/5MKFB3n2u5c/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Honda CR-Z Will Get Mugen-ized (In Japan, Anyway)'),
