(2938, '3', '2022-12-16 22:57:29', '<img src=\"http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/2010_NAIAS_Hybrid_Concept_1-440x293.jpg\" alt=\"Toyota 2010 NAIAS Hybrid Concept\" />\nIt’s auto-show teasing time; Toyota will show a new dedicated hybrid concept vehicle in Detroit this coming January. We get two clipped shots to whet our appetites.\n\n\nWhat we do see is a vehicle with a stubby front end that looks suspiciously like that of Toyota’s iQ minicar—our bet is that this concept is based on [...]\n\n\nRelated posts:2010 Toyota Prius Plug-In Hybrid Concept – Official Photos and InfoFerrari to Show Hybrid ConceptToyota Camry CNG Hybrid Concept – Auto Shows...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/caranddriver/blog/~3/kqJelwmhGpI/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Toyota Teases Green (Literally) Dedicated Hybrid Concept Ahead of Detroit Show'),
(2939, '3', '2022-12-14 23:04:31', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/volvo_c30_front_wide_main_a.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\nVolvo announced today that its 2011 Volvo C30 T5 and C30 T5 R-Design will carry a price-tag of $24,600 and $26,950 respectively. Both models come standard with a 227-hp inline 5-cylinder turbocharged engine and a 6-speed manual transmission. Adding a 5-speed automatic transmission with Geartronic will cost you an extra $1,250.\nThe 2011 Volvo C30 T5 [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/IZDlxD6Ud30/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', '2011 Volvo C30 T5 prices start at $24,600'),
(2940, '3', '2022-12-14 22:49:13', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/chevrolet_wifi_wide_main_a.jpg\" alt=\"Chevrolet Wi-Fi\" />\nGeneral Motors announced today that it has teamed up with Autonet Mobile to provide Wi-Fi capabilities for Chevrolet vehicles. The new dealer installed feature allows full Internet access inside and up to a 150 feet radius around the vehicle.\n“Chevrolet Wi-Fi by Autonet Mobile enhances commuting, family vacations and work,” says Chris Rauser, Chevrolet Accessories Manager. [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/QUFeho_LRI4/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'GM and Autonet team up to provide Wi-Fi for Chevrolet vehicles'),
(2941, '3', '2022-12-14 22:39:51', '<img src=\"http://www.egmcartech.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/honda_element_wide_main_a.jpg\" alt=\"Honda Element\" />\nEven though the Honda Element has been a disappointing seller, Honda plans on going forward with a second-generation of its crazy crossover rather than phasing it out. According to John Mendel, American Honda Motor Co. executive vice president, Honda is hitting a key demographic with the Element that it can’t with the SUV’s platform sibling, [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/egmcartech/~3/UEr1vAJuyoE/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Honda Element to see second-generation despite disappointing sales'),
(2942, '3', '2022-12-14 22:32:03', '<img src=\"http://www.carzi.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Lamborghini-Toro-Concept.jpg\" alt=\"Lamborghini Toro Concept\" />\n\n\n\n\nThe Lamborghini Toro LA690-4 is a modern concept interpretation of the 1960 Lamborghini Espada aimed to compete against the Aston Martin One 77 and the newly minted Lexus LFA.  \nThe designer Amadou Ndiaye stated that the LA 690-4 designation stands for “Longitudinale Anteriore” which translates to “Front Longitudinal” in English, while “690? refers to [...]...<br><a href=\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Carzi/~3/EWygcko2UpY/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feedproxy.google.com</a><br>', 'Lamborghini Toro Concept Photos'),
(2943, '3', '2022-12-14 14:38:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/uk.autoblog.com/media/2009/12/sa5285---angle_450.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Gadgets, Toys, Accessories When we were young, a long road trip was akin to torture. If you were lucky enough to avoid travel sickness, chances are death by I-spy or choking on a piece of magnetic chess were on the cards! Kids these days have it easy. Just take a look at this smart MP4 player. The Philips SA5285 is a clever portable media player that lets users download video from a PC to watch on the move. It boasts an impressive 8GB memory, which is enough room for 1,800 songs or 35 hours of rubbish kids TV.\r\nLittle ones in the back will be amused by Sponge Bob, marvelling at th...<br><a href=\"http://uk.autoblog.com/2009/12/14/gadget-gifts-philips-sa5285/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: uk.autoblog.com</a><br>', 'Gadget gifts: Philips SA5285'),
