(3427, '0', '2022-12-17 17:49:08', '\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nGeneral Motors’ GMC division announced on Thursday it will be extending its Denali luxury trim level to the Acadia crossover for the 2011 model year.  The Denali package first appeared in the GMC lineup in 1999 and has proven to be a popular – and profitable – option.\n \n Set to go on sale [...]\n\n\n...<br><a href=\"http://feeds.leftlanenews.com/click.phdo?i=bcac01bb88eb641066addf66cb6b68df\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: feeds.leftlanenews.com</a><br>', 'GMC announces Acadia Denali for 2011MY'),
(3428, '0', '2022-12-17 22:31:28', 'General Motors Chairman and interim CEO Ed Whitacre gave an official statement recently. GM is said to repay its government loans entirely by the end of June. This boils down to GM currently owing the U.S. Treasury about $6.7 billion dollars.\nGM’s cash can amount to $42.6 billion at the end of the third quarter. However, [...]...<br><a href=\"http://www.4wheelsnews.com/report-gm-to-repay-its-government-loans-entirely-by-the-end-of-june/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: www.4wheelsnews.com</a><br>', 'Report: GM to repay its government loans entirely by the end of June'),
