(3512, '0', '2022-12-18 07:40:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/uk.autoblog.com/media/2009/12/v12_black.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Aston Martin, Coupes, Sports/GTs, News \r\nAston Martin is launching special edition versions of its range-topping DBS and V12 Vantage models called the Carbon Black. \r\nBoth cars get Carbon Black bodywork, which is hand painted and takes 50 hours to apply. They also receive diamond cut alloy wheels with gloss black detailing and a bright finished grille and parking sensors.\r\nInside, the Carbon Black theme continues with lightweight black leather seats with contrasting silver stitching - hand stitched - piano black trim throughout the cabin and black anodised pedals. The V12 Vantage ...<br><a href=\"http://uk.autoblog.com/2009/12/18/aston-martin-announces-carbon-black-special-editions/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: uk.autoblog.com</a><br>', 'Aston Martin announces Carbon Black Special Editions'),
(3513, '0', '2022-12-18 07:32:00', '<img src=\"http://www.blogcdn.com/uk.autoblog.com/media/2009/12/climax.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Filed under: Sports/GTs, Supercars, UK, News A British-built supercar is aiming to challenge the likes of the Ariel Atom and the Caparo T1 when it goes on sale in 2010.The production version of the Climax Sports Racer will cost £92,000, and exclusivity is guaranteed as only 200 are expected to be built by the Coventry-based outfit.The lightweight racer is capable of getting to 60mph in as little as 3.7 seconds and keeps going all the way to 170mph. It manages this thanks to the combination of a 345 bhp 4.6-litre V8 engine and the option of a supercharger that takes power up to 450bhp.Suc...<br><a href=\"http://uk.autoblog.com/2009/12/18/climax-set-to-take-on-ariel-atom-and-caparo/\" target=\"_blank\">Fuente Original: uk.autoblog.com</a><br>', 'Climax set to take on Ariel Atom and Caparo'),
